	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Costume_Design" title="Academy Award for Costume Design">Best Costume Design, Black-and-White</a> - <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julie_Harris_(costume_designer)" title="Julie Harris (costume designer)">Julie Harris</a></li>
	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Writing_Original_Screenplay" title="Academy Award for Writing Original Screenplay">Best Writing, Story and Screenplay - Written Directly for the Screen</a> - <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederic_Raphael" title="Frederic Raphael">Frederic Raphael</a>.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Directing" title="Academy Award for Directing">Best Director</a> - John Schlesinger</li>
	<li><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Picture" title="Academy Award for Best Picture">Best Picture</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The movie was nominated for six <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BAFTA_Awards" title="BAFTA Awards">BAFTA Awards</a> and won four: Best British Actress -<a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julie_Christie" title="Julie Christie">Julie Christie</a>; Best British Actor - <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirk_Bogarde" title="Dirk Bogarde">Dirk Bogarde</a>; Best British Art Direction - <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Ray_Simm&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" title="Ray Simm (page does not exist)">Ray Simm</a>; and Best British Screenplay - <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederic_Raphael" title="Frederic Raphael">Frederic Raphael</a>.</p>
